OL,3,CWhat is a 'thundery breakdown' and why
OL,4,Cdo we get it after hot weather?
OL,6,FInstead, a 'shower' refers to a
OL,7,Fhaphazardly forming spell of rain - be
OL,8,Fit light or heavy, short or prolonged
OL,9,F- that forms away from an organised
OL,10,Fband of rain along a frontal system
OL,11,Feg. a cold, warm or occluded front
OL,12,F(blue, red or purple respectively on a
OL,13,Fweather map).
OL,15,FShowers, instead, are very localised
OL,16,Fand form randomly in unstable air,
OL,17,Fwhich is why it can be tipping it down
OL,18,Fwith rain in one area, and bone dry
OL,19,Fjust a mile away!
