OL,3,CWhat is a 'thundery breakdown' and why
OL,4,Cdo we get it after hot weather?
OL,6,FThey are generated by localised
OL,7,Fheating of the Earth's surface, which
OL,8,Fcauses warm air to rise, cool, and
OL,9,Fcondense into clouds. Unlike 'frontal
OL,10,Frain', showers often start and stop
OL,11,Fvery suddenly.
OL,13,FWhen we get intense heating of the
OL,14,FEarth, during a prolonged hot spell,
OL,15,Fthis warming air rises higher and
OL,16,Ffaster than normal and creates huge,
OL,17,Ftowering thunderclouds like giant
OL,18,Fskyscrapers in the air.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
