OL,3,CWhat is a 'thundery breakdown' and why
OL,4,Cdo we get it after hot weather?
OL,6,FThe water droplets in the air quickly
OL,7,Ffreeze into balls of ice (hail) and,
OL,8,Fas they rapidly circulate within the
OL,9,Fthundercloud, they knock into each
OL,10,Fother, creating static electricity.
OL,12,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,13,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,14,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,15,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,17,FEventually, the buildup of electricity
OL,18,Fis such that it discharges either
OL,19,Fbetween clouds or from the clouds down
OL,20,Fto the ground.
