OL,3,CWhat is a 'thundery breakdown' and why
OL,4,Cdo we get it after hot weather?
OL,6,FWe see this discharge as 'lightning'
OL,7,Fand the sound that it makes is
OL,8,Fthunder, which is caused by the
OL,9,Frapidly expanding air as the lightning
OL,10,Fmoves through it. Essentially, the
OL,11,Fgreater the heat near ground level,
OL,12,Fthe greater the chance of
OL,13,Fthunderstorms being created.
OL,15,FHave we already seen some
OL,16,Fthunderstorms in this hot spell?
